The woman and her boyfriend were travelling in his vehicle when four men attacked them. CAPE TOWN - Police are investigating an incident in which a woman was gang raped following a hijacking in Elsies River over the weekend. The woman and her boyfriend were travelling in his vehicle when four men attacked them in the early hours of Saturday morning.The suspects drove off with the woman still inside the vehicle.Western Cape police spokesperson Andre Traut explained what happened: They drove off with his Chana light delivery vehicle with his girlfriend still inside. She was raped by the suspects. No one has been arrested yet. (Edited by Shimoney Regter)